I"<p>Have you tried to write one of these before? They’re <a href="http://helentran.com/fouryearsoflessons">timestamps of your life</a> and can be a great way to remind yourself to be grateful for what has happened and what will happen.</p>

<p>I haven’t been secret about this year being difficult for me: I placed a lot of emphasis on my goals and not enough emphasis on what was making my heart beat. It was a year of bedding patience: how long does it take to build muscle? a team? a company?</p>

<hr class="--small" />

<h2 id="2019--the-year-of-heartbreaks">2019 – The Year of Heartbreaks</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Sometimes things don’t work out and that’s it.</li>
  <li>Wealth is peace of mind.</li>
  <li>Love isn’t returned in equal measure. Try anyway.</li>
  <li>Have faith in your resilience.</li>
  <li>High performance is consistency.</li>
  <li>Insecurity screams louder than talent or skill ever could.</li>
  <li>Missing someone does not mean you made the wrong decision.</li>
  <li>Stay sweet.</li>
</ol>
